HB 354 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Ventrella
Redesignates the Magnolia Bridge on LA Hwy. 64, over the Amite River at the boundary
of East Baton Rouge Parish and Livingston Parish as the "Caleb Easterling Memorial
Bridge".
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) or its contractors to erect and
maintain appropriate signage reflecting this bridge designation provided local or private
monies are received by the DOTD equal to its actual costs for material, fabrication,
mounting posts, and installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign.
